<p>With online banking, you can pay bills electronically from your UMB checking account to people and businesses across the U.S. Log in to your UMB online banking account to get started.</p>
<ul>
<li>One-time and recurring payments</li>
<li>Schedule payments for a future date</li>
<li>Review the due date and process time for payments</li>
<li>Convenient and quick payee set up</li>
<li>View payment history</li>

                            <div class="coh-container ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-58dfd052-7d84-4ad4-a2bf-db80d904d6e4 coh-component-instance-58dfd052-7d84-4ad4-a2bf-db80d904d6e4 no-padding coh-ce-cpt_3_column_layout-6264bd4d" >  <div class="coh-container coh-container-boxed" > <div class="coh-row coh-row-xl coh-row-visible-xl" data-coh-row-match-heights="[]"> <div class="coh-row-inner  coh-ce-cpt_3_column_layout-f68d7bf7"> <div class="coh-column ssa-instance-09d8ddb0fc16315e201d02b47f74473e coh-ce-cpt_3_column_layout-b31d779f coh-visible-sm coh-col-sm-12 coh-visible-xl coh-col-xl-4" >                 <div class="coh-container ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-475affd9-52a5-4381-9fe8-5fae7e4fb92b coh-component-instance-475affd9-52a5-4381-9fe8-5fae7e4fb92b no-padding coh-ce-cpt_read_more_layout-e2f3c1db" >  <div class="coh-container read-more coh-ce-cpt_read_more_layout-a42dc426 coh-container-boxed" > <h3 class="coh-heading coh-ce-cpt_read_more_layout-fca8d376"  > Consumer Overdraft Protection Line of Credit* </h3>  <div class="coh-wysiwyg content-collapsed coh-ce-cpt_read_more_layout-7951177f"  >    <p>Your activated Consumer Overdraft Protection Line of Credit operates similarly to a credit card, with a pre-authorized credit limit and an annual percentage rate. Consumer Overdraft Protection Line of Credit advances are for the exact amount that the account is overdrawn, bringing the account to a $0 available balance. Subject to credit approval.</p>
<p><span class="coh-style-paragraph-small">*Please see service terms and conditions for more information about the Overdraft Protection service.</span></p>
 </div>  <div class="coh-inline-element coh-ce-cpt_read_more_layout-3446b32"> <button class="coh-button read-more-btn plus coh-style-read-more-with-icon coh-ce-cpt_read_more_layout-7b59673f coh-interaction" data-interaction-modifiers="[{"interactionScope":"parent","modifierType":"add-modifier","interactionParent":".read-more","interactionTarget":".read-more","modifierName":"expanded"}]" data-coh-settings='{ "xl":{"buttonAnimation":[{"animationType":"none"}]} }' type="button"> Read more</button>  <button class="coh-button read-more-btn close coh-style-read-more-with-icon coh-ce-cpt_read_more_layout-e9387a93 coh-interaction" data-interaction-modifiers="[{"interactionScope":"parent","modifierType":"remove-modifier","interactionParent":".read-more","interactionTarget":".read-more","modifierName":"expanded"}]" data-coh-settings='{ "xl":{"buttonAnimation":[{"animationType":"none"}]} }' type="button"> Close</button> </div> </div> </div> 
   </div> <div class="coh-column ssa-instance-09d8ddb0fc16315e201d02b47f74473e coh-ce-cpt_3_column_layout-71b82af4 coh-visible-sm coh-col-sm-12 coh-visible-xl coh-col-xl-4" >                 <div class="coh-container ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-a7cbc7f7-d1cd-4405-9ef0-43cf18363783 coh-component-instance-a7cbc7f7-d1cd-4405-9ef0-43cf18363783 no-padding coh-ce-cpt_read_more_layout-e2f3c1db" >  <div class="coh-container read-more coh-ce-cpt_read_more_layout-a42dc426 coh-container-boxed" > <h3 class="coh-heading coh-ce-cpt_read_more_layout-fca8d376"  > Credit Card Overdraft Protection* </h3>  <div class="coh-wysiwyg content-collapsed coh-ce-cpt_read_more_layout-7951177f"  >    <p>UMB offers Credit Card Overdraft Protection for individuals who have been approved for a UMB credit card and wish to authorize funds to be made available in their checking account up to their available credit limit. Credit Card Overdraft Protection advances occur in $100 increments, up to available credit limit.  If available credit limit is less than $100, the available amount will be advanced. Subject to credit approval.</p>
<p><span class="coh-style-paragraph-small">*Please see service terms and conditions for more information about the Overdraft Protection service.</span></p>

            <div class="coh-accordion-title" data-coh-tab-settings='[]'><a href="#230548828-2671742319" >Where is my account number on a check?</a></div> <div id="230548828-2671742319" class="coh-accordion-tabs-content ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-6fadffd9-8074-43f0-a916-c20b0e593705 coh-component-instance-6fadffd9-8074-43f0-a916-c20b0e593705 coh-ce-cpt_accordion_item-4f4205ef"  >  <div class="coh-container coh-style-padding-small" >              <div class="coh-wysiwyg ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-5b160a9b-8ebd-42bc-be2c-3edb1f525b84 coh-component-instance-5b160a9b-8ebd-42bc-be2c-3edb1f525b84  coh-style-text-color-light-background        ssa-instance-17f1909d7a163496622312a220123968 coh-ce-cpt_text-fa10298a"  >    <p>Your checking account number is at the bottom of a personal check. It’s usually the longest number (typically 10-12 digits) printed in a series of numbers.</p>
<p>Look at this example from a UMB personal checking account. Here, the UMB account number is third in the series at the bottom: bank routing number, check number, account number.</p>
       <article class="align-center">  <picture> <source srcset="/sites/default/files/styles/coh_x_large/public/2023-05/check-properties.jpg?itok=N1Yv5KdR" media="(min-width: 1440px)" type="image/jpeg"> <source srcset="/sites/default/files/styles/coh_x_large/public/2023-05/check-properties.jpg?itok=N1Yv5KdR" media="(min-width: 1170px) and (max-width: 1439px)" type="image/jpeg"> <source srcset="/sites/default/files/styles/coh_x_large/public/2023-05/check-properties.jpg?itok=N1Yv5KdR" media="(min-width: 1024px) and (max-width: 1169px)" type="image/jpeg"> <source srcset="/sites/default/files/styles/coh_medium/public/2023-05/check-properties.jpg?itok=w2t1VDIg" media="(min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 1023px)" type="image/jpeg"> <source srcset="/sites/default/files/styles/coh_small/public/2023-05/check-properties.jpg?itok=-q8tbggX" media="(min-width: 565px) and (max-width: 767px)" type="image/jpeg"> <source srcset="/sites/default/files/styles/coh_small/public/2023-05/check-properties.jpg?itok=-q8tbggX" media="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 564px)" type="image/jpeg"> <img class="coh-image coh-image-responsive-xl coh-image-responsive-sm coh-image-responsive-ps" src="/sites/default/files/styles/coh_x_large/public/2023-05/check-properties.jpg?itok=N1Yv5KdR" title alt="How to find the account number on a check"> </picture> </article> 
 </div> 
   </div> </div> 
            <div class="coh-accordion-title" data-coh-tab-settings='[]'><a href="#230548828-4117067868" >Does opening a checking account affect my credit score?</a></div> <div id="230548828-4117067868" class="coh-accordion-tabs-content ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-e61f411c-e449-45fe-ac1f-c83ecfd8b61c coh-component-instance-e61f411c-e449-45fe-ac1f-c83ecfd8b61c coh-ce-cpt_accordion_item-4f4205ef"  >  <div class="coh-container coh-style-padding-small" >              <div class="coh-wysiwyg ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-472b265a-332b-4bfc-bf01-02e75a4892df coh-component-instance-472b265a-332b-4bfc-bf01-02e75a4892df  coh-style-text-color-light-background        ssa-instance-f5700ba0a5ef0c2b7b02989da1b741bf coh-ce-cpt_text-fa10298a"  >    <p>Usually, opening a checking account does not affect your credit score. A bank might look at your credit report when you apply to open a bank account. But this is typically a “soft inquiry,” which doesn’t impact your credit score.</p>
<p>If a bank uses a “hard inquiry” to review your credit report, the negative impact to your credit score is still relatively low. </p>
 </div> 
   </div> </div> 
            <div class="coh-accordion-title" data-coh-tab-settings='[]'><a href="#230548828-2729918499" >What do I need to open a checking account?</a></div> <div id="230548828-2729918499" class="coh-accordion-tabs-content ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-e7e2c707-7c72-47c1-b4ea-21b0dfd72b86 coh-component-instance-e7e2c707-7c72-47c1-b4ea-21b0dfd72b86 coh-ce-cpt_accordion_item-4f4205ef"  >  <div class="coh-container coh-style-padding-small" >              <div class="coh-wysiwyg ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-2cc34131-62a2-4cd9-b833-dfbee9fb1772 coh-component-instance-2cc34131-62a2-4cd9-b833-dfbee9fb1772  coh-style-text-color-light-background        ssa-instance-736bad1b191d7c966ff00a569feca5de coh-ce-cpt_text-fa10298a"  >    <p>Here are a few things you’ll need to open a personal checking account:</p>
<ol>
<li>A state-issued ID, driver’s license or learner’s permit. If you do not have these forms of identification, please contact a nearby UMB branch for more information about forms of identification accepted in branch.</li>
<li>Basic personal information, including your birthdate, Social Security Number (SSN) or Tax ID Number (TIN), address and phone number.</li>
<li>An initial deposit may be required to open the account. Banks usually offer a variety of checking account options with different requirements for initial deposits.</li>
</ol>
<p>In some situations, you might also need:</p>
<ol start="4">
<li>IDs and personal information for other applicants if you want to open a joint account. A joint account is owned by multiple people, so a bank requires information from anyone sharing the account.</li>
<li>A co-owner or co-signer if you are younger than 18. A parent or legal guardian will need to sign legal documents for the bank.</li>
</ol>
 </div> 
   </div> </div> 
            <div class="coh-accordion-title" data-coh-tab-settings='[]'><a href="#230548828-3942113086" >Can I open a checking account online?</a></div> <div id="230548828-3942113086" class="coh-accordion-tabs-content ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-0b666659-79e4-47e4-8371-d2c93ae5c8c3 coh-component-instance-0b666659-79e4-47e4-8371-d2c93ae5c8c3 coh-ce-cpt_accordion_item-4f4205ef"  >  <div class="coh-container coh-style-padding-small" >              <div class="coh-wysiwyg ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-27de31ae-fcab-41e2-bbce-f216c8c92c0f coh-component-instance-27de31ae-fcab-41e2-bbce-f216c8c92c0f  coh-style-text-color-light-background        ssa-instance-6495bf0358214fec351866f6da49a53d coh-ce-cpt_text-fa10298a"  >    <p>Yes, you can open a checking account online. Most banks provide a simple and secure online bank account application process. To open a UMB account online, you must:</p>
<ol>
<li>Be at least 18 years old.</li>
<li>Be a U.S. citizen or resident alien.</li>
<li>Live in Arizona, Colorado, Illinois, Kansas, Missouri, Nebraska, Oklahoma or Texas.</li>
<li>Have a state ID, driver’s license or learner’s permit.</li>
</ol>
<p>You can get started with UMB today. It takes just a few minutes to apply for and open a UMB personal checking account.</p>
 </div> 
   </div> </div> 
            <div class="coh-accordion-title" data-coh-tab-settings='[]'><a href="#230548828-920350854" >How do I check my account balance?</a></div> <div id="230548828-920350854" class="coh-accordion-tabs-content ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-f2bdb51c-4ee2-47f8-8c98-e45f60dd3b87 coh-component-instance-f2bdb51c-4ee2-47f8-8c98-e45f60dd3b87 coh-ce-cpt_accordion_item-4f4205ef"  >  <div class="coh-container coh-style-padding-small" >              <div class="coh-wysiwyg ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-3d3735fa-d765-4a36-a323-03785f917cc7 coh-component-instance-3d3735fa-d765-4a36-a323-03785f917cc7  coh-style-text-color-light-background        ssa-instance-9f0be3e08268690108c5f6586b3d3b07 coh-ce-cpt_text-fa10298a"  >    <p>Checking your account balance regularly is a great way to track your spending habits and financial goals. Here’s how to check your UMB account balance:</p>
<ol>
<li><a href="/personal-banking/banking-with-us/mobile-banking">Download the UMB mobile banking</a> app for on-the-go account access.</li>
<li><a href="/personal-banking/banking-with-us/online-banking">Visit umb.com/onlinebanking</a>. To register for online banking, you’ll need your account number and personal information.</li>
<li>Call 800.860.4UMB (4862) to hear your account balance or speak to a representative at the UMB Service Center. You’ll need to activate your direct banking access the first time you call.</li>
<li><a href="https://locations.umb.com">Stop by the nearest UMB branch or ATM</a>. Have your ID with you, and a UMB personal banker will be happy to help you at a branch. You can also check account balances using your UMB card and PIN at an ATM.</li>
<li>Enroll in paperless statements through UMB Online Banking to have account statements conveniently emailed to you.</li>
</ol>
 </div> 
   </div> </div> 
            <div class="coh-accordion-title" data-coh-tab-settings='[]'><a href="#230548828-245105249" >Do checking accounts earn interest?</a></div> <div id="230548828-245105249" class="coh-accordion-tabs-content ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-af744eab-c33b-4a3d-b80b-d53f7a18b7aa coh-component-instance-af744eab-c33b-4a3d-b80b-d53f7a18b7aa coh-ce-cpt_accordion_item-4f4205ef"  >  <div class="coh-container coh-style-padding-small" >              <div class="coh-wysiwyg ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-6258f656-e8d5-4fe2-a5e8-6f95bc629169 coh-component-instance-6258f656-e8d5-4fe2-a5e8-6f95bc629169  coh-style-text-color-light-background        ssa-instance-fa5026a16e8a59474c43becbec7cb2f1 coh-ce-cpt_text-fa10298a"  >    <p>Yes, certain checking accounts can earn interest. Interest-bearing checking accounts usually require a higher minimum opening deposit. Banks often offer fee waivers if you make larger initial deposits or maintain higher balances.</p>
<p>If you’d like to earn interest on your account at UMB, consider opening a <strong>UMB Select Checking account</strong>. This account type also offers access to special loan rate discounts.</p>
<p>If an interest-bearing checking account isn’t right for you, we also offer UMB Value Checking and UMB Free Checking. Find the best fit for you by comparing UMB personal checking account options.</p>
 </div> 
   </div> </div> 
            <div class="coh-accordion-title" data-coh-tab-settings='[]'><a href="#230548828-1702619593" >How do I reorder checks?</a></div> <div id="230548828-1702619593" class="coh-accordion-tabs-content ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-742abe6f-81e7-40dd-8e84-aae581074d68 coh-component-instance-742abe6f-81e7-40dd-8e84-aae581074d68 coh-ce-cpt_accordion_item-4f4205ef"  >  <div class="coh-container coh-style-padding-small" >                  <div class="coh-wysiwyg ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-ddecf983-cd5b-4930-9d0b-d099cee6d101 coh-component-instance-ddecf983-cd5b-4930-9d0b-d099cee6d101  coh-style-text-color-light-background        ssa-instance-5417549f1797af1130e71177181b1579 coh-ce-cpt_text-fa10298a"  >    <p>To reorder checks for your UMB account, you can:</p>
<ul>
<li>Order through online banking. Log in to your account to access the order dashboard.</li>
<li><a href="https://orderpoint.deluxe.com/personal-checks/welcome.htm">Order online through Deluxe Financial Services, Inc. </a><img style="background:#fff;display:inline-block;padding:2px;width:15px;" src="/sites/default/files/2023-08/Leave.svg" alt="leaving website icon"></li>
<li>Order at a <a href="https://locations.umb.com/">branch or connect with us</a> to get started (best for first-time check orders or information changes)</li>
</ul>
 </div> 
   </div> </div>

Overdraft Protection Services 
Consumer Overdraft Protection Line of Credit* 
Your activated Consumer Overdraft Protection Line of Credit operates
similarly to a credit card, with a pre-authorized credit limit and an annual
percentage rate. Consumer Overdraft Protection Line of Credit advances
are for the exact amount that the account is overdrawn, bringing the
account to a $0 available balance. Subject to credit approval.
*Please see service terms and conditions for more information about the
Overdraft Protection service.
 Read more
 Close
Credit Card Overdraft Protection* 
UMB offers Credit Card Overdraft Protection for individuals who have been
approved for a UMB credit card and wish to authorize funds to be made
available in their checking account up to their available credit limit. Credit
Card Overdraft Protection advances occur in $100 increments, up to
available credit limit.  If available credit limit is less than $100, the
available amount will be advanced. Subject to credit approval.

Which checking account is best for me?

body_pages.17:
Finding the right checking account is all about the features you want. Look
for features that make accessing your money easier, whether it’s online
banking, ATM and branch locations, or special services like money orders
and Cashier’s Checks.
Where is my account number on a check?
Your checking account number is at the bottom of a personal check. It’s
usually the longest number (typically 10-12 digits) printed in a series of
numbers.
Look at this example from a UMB personal checking account. Here, the
UMB account number is third in the series at the bottom: bank routing
number, check number, account number.
Does opening a checking account affect my credit score?
Usually, opening a checking account does not affect your credit score. A
bank might look at your credit report when you apply to open a bank
account. But this is typically a “soft inquiry,” which doesn’t impact your
credit score.
If a bank uses a “hard inquiry” to review your credit report, the negative
impact to your credit score is still relatively low. 
What do I need to open a checking account?
Here are a few things you’ll need to open a personal checking account:
A state-issued ID, driver’s license or learner’s permit. If you do not
have these forms of identification, please contact a nearby UMB
branch for more information about forms of identification accepted in
branch.
Basic personal information, including your birthdate, Social Security
Number (SSN) or Tax ID Number (TIN), address and phone number.
An initial deposit may be required to open the account. Banks usually
offer a variety of checking account options with different requirements
for initial deposits.
In some situations, you might also need:
IDs and personal information for other applicants if you want to open a
joint account. A joint account is owned by multiple people, so a bank
requires information from anyone sharing the account.
A co-owner or co-signer if you are younger than 18. A parent or legal
guardian will need to sign legal documents for the bank.
Can I open a checking account online?

body_pages.18:
Yes, you can open a checking account online. Most banks provide a simple
and secure online bank account application process. To open a UMB
account online, you must:
Be at least 18 years old.
Be a U.S. citizen or resident alien.
Live in Arizona, Colorado, Illinois, Kansas, Missouri, Nebraska,
Oklahoma or Texas.
Have a state ID, driver’s license or learner’s permit.
You can get started with UMB today. It takes just a few minutes to apply for
and open a UMB personal checking account.
How do I check my account balance?
Checking your account balance regularly is a great way to track your
spending habits and financial goals. Here’s how to check your UMB account
balance:
Download the UMB mobile banking app for on-the-go account access.
Visit umb.com/onlinebanking. To register for online banking, you’ll
need your account number and personal information.
Call 800.860.4UMB (4862) to hear your account balance or speak to a
representative at the UMB Service Center. You’ll need to activate your
direct banking access the first time you call.
Stop by the nearest UMB branch or ATM. Have your ID with you, and a
UMB personal banker will be happy to help you at a branch. You can
also check account balances using your UMB card and PIN at an ATM.
Enroll in paperless statements through UMB Online Banking to have
account statements conveniently emailed to you.
Do checking accounts earn interest?
Yes, certain checking accounts can earn interest. Interest-bearing checking
accounts usually require a higher minimum opening deposit. Banks often
offer fee waivers if you make larger initial deposits or maintain higher
balances.
If you’d like to earn interest on your account at UMB, consider opening a 
UMB Select Checking account. This account type also offers access to
special loan rate discounts.
If an interest-bearing checking account isn’t right for you, we also offer
UMB Value Checking and UMB Free Checking. Find the best fit for you by
comparing UMB personal checking account options.
How do I reorder checks?
To reorder checks for your UMB account, you can:
Order through online banking. Log in to your account to access the
order dashboard.

Overdraft Protection Services 
Consumer Overdraft Protection Line of Credit* 
Your activated Consumer Overdraft Protection Line of Credit operates
similarly to a credit card, with a pre-authorized credit limit and an annual
percentage rate. Consumer Overdraft Protection Line of Credit advances
are for the exact amount that the account is overdrawn, bringing the
account to a $0 available balance. Subject to credit approval.

Credit Card Overdraft Protection* 
UMB offers Credit Card Overdraft Protection for individuals who have been
approved for a UMB credit card and wish to authorize funds to be made
available in their checking account up to their available credit limit. Credit
Card Overdraft Protection advances occur in $100 increments, up to
available credit limit.  If available credit limit is less than $100, the
available amount will be advanced. Subject to credit approval.

FAQs 
Questions about your Checking Account?
UMB has answers. 
Which checking account is best for me?
• Heloc
• unexpected financial windfall
Personal (126)
financial education (486), financial plan
Apply
Finding the right checking account is all about the features you want. Look
for features that make accessing your money easier, whether it’s online
banking, ATM and branch locations, or special services like money orders
and Cashier’s Checks.
Where is my account number on a check?
Your checking account number is at the bottom of a personal check. It’s
usually the longest number (typically 10-12 digits) printed in a series of
numbers.
Look at this example from a UMB personal checking account. Here, the
UMB account number is third in the series at the bottom: bank routing
number, check number, account number.
Does opening a checking account affect my credit score?
Usually, opening a checking account does not affect your credit score. A
bank might look at your credit report when you apply to open a bank
account. But this is typically a “soft inquiry,” which doesn’t impact your
credit score.
If a bank uses a “hard inquiry” to review your credit report, the negative
impact to your credit score is still relatively low. 
What do I need to open a checking account?
Here are a few things you’ll need to open a personal checking account:
A state-issued ID, driver’s license or learner’s permit. If you do not
have these forms of identification, please contact a nearby UMB
branch for more information about forms of identification accepted in
branch.
Basic personal information, including your birthdate, Social Security
Number (SSN) or Tax ID Number (TIN), address and phone number.
An initial deposit may be required to open the account. Banks usually
offer a variety of checking account options with different requirements
for initial deposits.
In some situations, you might also need:
IDs and personal information for other applicants if you want to open a
joint account. A joint account is owned by multiple people, so a bank
requires information from anyone sharing the account.
A co-owner or co-signer if you are younger than 18. A parent or legal
guardian will need to sign legal documents for the bank.
Can I open a checking account online?

Yes, you can open a checking account online. Most banks provide a simple
and secure online bank account application process. To open a UMB
account online, you must:
Be at least 18 years old.
Be a U.S. citizen or resident alien.
Live in Arizona, Colorado, Illinois, Kansas, Missouri, Nebraska,
Oklahoma or Texas.
Have a state ID, driver’s license or learner’s permit.
You can get started with UMB today. It takes just a few minutes to apply for
and open a UMB personal checking account.
How do I check my account balance?
Checking your account balance regularly is a great way to track your
spending habits and financial goals. Here’s how to check your UMB account
balance:
Download the UMB mobile banking app for on-the-go account access.
Visit umb.com/onlinebanking. To register for online banking, you’ll
need your account number and personal information.
Call 800.860.4UMB (4862) to hear your account balance or speak to a
representative at the UMB Service Center. You’ll need to activate your
direct banking access the first time you call.
Stop by the nearest UMB branch or ATM. Have your ID with you, and a
UMB personal banker will be happy to help you at a branch. You can
also check account balances using your UMB card and PIN at an ATM.
Enroll in paperless statements through UMB Online Banking to have
account statements conveniently emailed to you.
Do checking accounts earn interest?
Yes, certain checking accounts can earn interest. Interest-bearing checking
accounts usually require a higher minimum opening deposit. Banks often
offer fee waivers if you make larger initial deposits or maintain higher
balances.
If you’d like to earn interest on your account at UMB, consider opening a 
UMB Select Checking account. This account type also offers access to
special loan rate discounts.
If an interest-bearing checking account isn’t right for you, we also offer
UMB Value Checking and UMB Free Checking. Find the best fit for you by
comparing UMB personal checking account options.
How do I reorder checks?
To reorder checks for your UMB account, you can:
Order through online banking. Log in to your account to access the
order dashboard.
